The paper discusses the future of spreadsheet technology and its evolution in the context of Big Data, increased end-user computing, and mobile computing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it focuses on the interaction between users and spreadsheet technology. Additionally, the paper discusses the storage and manipulation of data, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also touches on the security and privacy concerns related to the use of spreadsheets, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for further research in the evolution and use of spreadsheets, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of these trends for end-users, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category, as it touches on the use of spreadsheets as a programming tool.
